18
00:01:33,100 --> 00:01:36,060
{\an2}{\pos(211.4,244.05)}第三季  第五集

19
00:01:45,270 --> 00:01:47,370
《斯塔福德法案》第一条
"Title One of the Stafford Act:

20
00:01:47,370 --> 00:01:50,820
"紧急情况"是指由总统指定的
'Emergency' means any occasion or instance for which,

21
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:52,930
场合或情形...
in the determination of the president..."

22
00:01:52,930 --> 00:01:55,420
指定权在总统
"Determined" by the president.

23
00:01:55,420 --> 00:01:57,630
-有先例吗  -只要我们能说明这些措施
- Any instance? - As long as we can make the argument

24
00:01:57,630 --> 00:02:00,100
能拯救生命  保护人民安康就行
that this saves lives and protects health and safety.

25
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:01,940
失业导致犯罪
Well, unemployment leads to crime,

26
00:02:01,940 --> 00:02:04,770
营养不良  以及恶劣的医疗服务
to malnutrition, to improper medical care.

27
00:02:04,770 --> 00:02:07,450
这种说法肯定会在法庭上遭到攻击的
There's no doubt it'll be challenged in the courts.

28
00:02:07,450 --> 00:02:09,220
就算最终闹上了法庭
Well, even so, by the time that happens,

29
00:02:09,220 --> 00:02:11,790
那时人们也会见识到《美国就业法案》了
people will see what America Works looks like.

30
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:15,390
告诉我  从法律的角度说
Tell me, in your legal opinion...

31
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:18,020
你们觉得有足够的回旋余地吗
is there enough leeway here?

32
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:20,180
有的  法案用词足够模糊
Yes, the language is sufficiently vague.

33
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:23,230
不过得说清楚  这么做实在是前所未有
But just to be clear, this is completely unorthodox.

34
00:02:23,230 --> 00:02:25,990
从没有哪个总统试过这么筹集资金
No president has ever tried to reappropriate funds this way.

35
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,210
谢谢各位  有这话就够了
Thank you, gentlemen, that's all I need.

36
00:02:30,070 --> 00:02:32,940
各州不会支持的  太激进了
The states won't go for this. Too radical.

37
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:34,620
哪怕有一个我联系的州长
And if I call just one governor

38
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:37,130
拒绝了我然后向媒体泄露了风声
who says no and leaks it to the press,

39
00:02:37,130 --> 00:02:40,900
还没等我正式提出  就会被国会穷追猛打
Congress will be on my ass before I get this out of the gates.

40
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:43,160
但是  哥伦比亚特区
But, the District of Columbia...

41
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:46,610
-没有州长  -只有你  一个市长
- No governor. - Just you, the mayor.

42
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:49,050
巴尼  我知道这会让你冒很大风险
Now, Barney, I know this puts you out on a ledge.

43
00:02:49,050 --> 00:02:52,370
我喜欢  每个条款我都支持
I love it. I love everything about it.

44
00:02:53,380 --> 00:02:57,400
我们年年都要为预算的每一分钱跟国会争
We have to fight Congress for every dollar in our budget, each year.

45
00:02:57,860 --> 00:03:01,150
如果选民看到我从他们嘴里抠出钱来
If my people see me take the money they won't give us...

46
00:03:01,870 --> 00:03:03,540
我就能赢得连任
well, I just won reelection.

47
00:03:03,980 --> 00:03:06,380
这就是让巴尼·豪尔这样的强人当选的原因
This is why you put a brawler like Barney Hull in office,

48
00:03:06,380 --> 00:03:08,520
不只是还他人情
aside from paying a debt.

49
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:11,980
把全美50位州长和535位国会议员加起来
Add up 50 governors and 535 members of Congress,

50
00:03:11,980 --> 00:03:15,370
也赶不上一位有进取心的大胆市长
you don't come close to the gumption of one bold mayor.

51
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:18,630
我希望全城各处的人都去注册找工作
I want people registering for jobs in every part of the city

52
00:03:18,630 --> 00:03:21,290
越快越好  趁法院还没发难
as soon as possible, before the court challenges bubble up.

53
00:03:21,290 --> 00:03:24,360
在国会门口支个大帐篷怎么样
What about one big tent right in front of the Capitol?

54
00:03:24,650 --> 00:03:25,950
让国会看看民众
Make Congress see the people

55
00:03:25,950 --> 00:03:28,330
排队找工作排到林肯纪念堂的场面
line up all the way back to the Lincoln Memorial.

56
00:03:28,330 --> 00:03:30,290
能在国庆日出手吗
Can we do something by July Fourth?

57
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:33,530
你只管放烟花  我找人来捧场
You bring the fireworks, I'll bring the people.

58
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:40,260
早上好  请坐
Good morning. Please, sit.

59
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:42,580
我知道雷米已经向各位介绍过情况了
I know Remy has just briefed you all,

60
00:03:42,580 --> 00:03:44,850
那么除了国土安全部部长
so, aside from the Secretary of Homeland Security,

61
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:48,420
已经离职之外  还有谁持反对意见吗
who is no longer with us, does anyone else object to this plan?

62
00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:52,090
很好  在新国安部长上任之前
Good. Until a new secretary is confirmed,

63
00:03:52,090 --> 00:03:54,920
联邦应急管理署将直接对我负责  谢谢各位
FEMA will report directly to me. Thank you all very much.

64
00:03:57,070 --> 00:04:01,160
美国国土安全部

65
00:03:57,070 --> 00:04:01,160
{\pos(232.5,184.05)}联邦应急管理署

66
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,760
{\pos(197.1,63)}联邦应急管理署署长
阿诺德·希尔瓦

67
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:13,160
失业不能
Unemployment doesn't

68
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:15,670
算作是自然灾害  总统先生
constitute a natural disaster, Mr. President.

69
00:04:15,670 --> 00:04:17,840
《斯塔福德法案》授权我
The Stafford Act gives me full authority

70
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:19,620
定义紧急状况
to define an emergency.

71
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:22,190
但是  先生  我们的赈灾基金
But, sir, we've only got about three billion left

72
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:23,570
只剩下30亿不到了
in the Disaster Relief Fund,

73
00:04:23,570 --> 00:04:25,280
而飓风季眼看就要来了
and we're about to go into hurricane season.

74
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:27,000
我们先用这现成的30亿
So we use the three billion that's there,

75
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,100
万一飓风来袭了
and if a hurricane hits,

76
00:04:28,110 --> 00:04:31,870
国会定会拨款补充赈灾基金  他们一向如此
Congress replenishes the funds, just as they always do.

77
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:35,320
灾害发生后  每分每秒都极其珍贵  先生
When it comes to a disaster, every hour counts, sir.

78
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:37,040
如果还得等国会那边
If we're waiting around for Congress--

79
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:39,970
希尔瓦先生  这事就这么定了
Mr. Silva, this is moving forward.

80
00:04:41,010 --> 00:04:42,520
平民会死伤惨重的  总统先生
People could die, Mr. President.

81
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:45,240
平民要是没工作  也会活不成的
People are dying because they don't have jobs.

82
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:48,530
虽然比死于地震洪水慢  但一样是死
Slower than a flood or an earthquake, but dying just the same.

83
00:04:48,530 --> 00:04:51,630
您怎么能拿失业和4级飓风相提并论
You can't compare unemployment to a cat four hurricane.

84
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:52,850
我来你办公室找你
I came to your office

85
00:04:52,850 --> 00:04:55,530
是希望你能继续坐在这个位子上
because I want this to remain your office.

86
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:58,160
连续三任总统都让你留任不是平白无故
There's a reason three presidents have kept you here.

87
00:04:58,160 --> 00:05:00,330
你专心致志  坚持不懈
You're dedicated, you're relentless,

88
00:05:00,330 --> 00:05:01,890
而且工作能力极为优秀
you're exceptionally competent.

89
00:05:01,890 --> 00:05:03,730
如果我们需要精打细算
If we have to stretch dollars even further,

90
00:05:03,730 --> 00:05:05,170
找你准没错
you're the man to do it.

91
00:05:05,170 --> 00:05:08,280
如果你走人了  就得找个没经验的了
It's either you or someone far less experienced.

92
00:05:10,340 --> 00:05:12,480
两位周末就要去爱荷华了
The two of you head to Iowa at the end of the week.

93
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:15,180
是的  这一趟要去18个郡拉票
That's right. Eighteen counties this trip.

94
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:18,110
{\pos(207.6,241.2)}{\pos(189.3,241.2)}希瑟·邓巴  民主党总统候选人

95
00:05:15,180 --> 00:05:18,600
希望一月之前能走遍全州99个郡
By January, I plan on hitting all 99.

96
00:05:18,820 --> 00:05:22,770
约翰会和我一起出席活动  直到他丈夫获释
John will join me at every event until his husband is released.

97
00:05:22,770 --> 00:05:25,300
自从迈克尔被捕后你和他联系过吗
Have you had any contact with Michael since his arrest?

98
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:29,750
{\pos(201,239.85)}{\pos(189.3,241.2)}迈克尔·帕斯特纳克
同性恋权利活动家迈克尔·科里根的丈夫

99
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:27,510
俄罗斯政府拒绝了
The Russian government has refused.

100
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,100
他们甚至不让他见律师
They won't let him speak to a lawyer.

101
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:31,190
所以约翰和我站在一起意义重大
That's why it's important John join me.

102
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:34,080
我们必须对莫斯科持续施压
We need to keep the pressure up on Moscow.

103
00:05:34,230 --> 00:05:35,580
在全国许多地方  同性恋权益
You know, gay rights is controversial

104
00:05:35,580 --> 00:05:36,820
都是极具争议性的话题
in many parts of the country.

105
00:05:36,820 --> 00:05:39,130
您不担心和科里根的丈夫站在一起
Do you think that appearing with Corrigan's husband

106
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:40,300
会对您的选情不利吗
could possibly hurt you?

107
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:43,670
我认为美国人民想要一位不逃避问题的候选人
I think the American people want a candidate who doesn't dodge,

108
00:05:43,670 --> 00:05:46,630
会诚实表达自己的立场
who is truthful about where she stands.

109
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:49,150
而不是回避争议
Not someone who shies away from controversy.

110
00:05:49,150 --> 00:05:51,140
回避争论是一回事
It's one thing to shy away from controversy.

111
00:05:51,140 --> 00:05:52,850
引发争论是另一回事
It's another thing to court it.

112
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:56,430
迈克尔因为直抒己见被捕
Well, Michael was arrested for speaking his mind.

113
00:05:56,430 --> 00:05:59,230
如果捍卫言论自由有争议  那么...
If defending free speech is controversial, then...

114
00:05:59,570 --> 00:06:01,170
我们不比俄罗斯好多少
we're no better than Russia.

115
00:06:01,220 --> 00:06:01,850
真希望我们的政府里
I wish that there were

116
00:06:01,850 --> 00:06:04,310
有更多人去捍卫言论自由
more people in our government defending it.

117
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:07,330
你指的是安德伍德政府吗
Are you talking specifically about the Underwood Administration?

118
00:06:07,410 --> 00:06:09,480
我认为总统可以采取更多措施
I think the president could do more.

119
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:12,170
白宫表示他们已经直接与
You know, the White House has said hat they've been speaking

120
00:06:12,170 --> 00:06:14,930
克里姆林宫方面沟通  他们原话是
directly with the Kremlin, that they, and I quote here:

121
00:06:14,930 --> 00:06:17,550
"必须解决这一问题  因为这关系到
"Have to tackle this issue as it relates to the larger

122
00:06:17,550 --> 00:06:20,660
两国之间更重要的外交关系"
diplomatic relationship between the two nations."

123
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:24,880
那我们为什么还没看到这些对话的证据呢
Then why haven't we seen any evidence of those talks?

124
00:06:24,890 --> 00:06:28,150
我当选总统后  美国人民可以放心
When I'm president, the American people can rest assured

125
00:06:28,150 --> 00:06:29,840
我会认真履行
that I will take my oath

126
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:34,440
捍卫和保护我们人民的誓言
to defend and protect our citizens seriously.

127
00:06:34,580 --> 00:06:37,830
-你觉得她怎么样  -什么  邓巴吗
- What do you think of her? - What, Dunbar?

128
00:06:38,050 --> 00:06:38,380
对
Yeah.

129
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:41,320
我认为这届政府做得还不够好
I believe that the administration could do better...

130
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:45,040
-你为安德伍德工作过  -现在不了
- You worked for Underwood. - Not anymore.

131
00:06:46,350 --> 00:06:47,730
我不会生气的
I won't be offended.

132
00:06:50,770 --> 00:06:53,200
我很喜欢她说的这些
Uh, I like a lot about what she has to say.

133
00:06:56,790 --> 00:06:57,970
你会投票给她吗
Would you vote for her?

134
00:06:59,650 --> 00:07:02,030
不知道  可能吧
I don't know. I might.

135
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:04,950
是啊  很可能会
Yeah. Probably would.

136
00:07:06,170 --> 00:07:07,760
-多快  -明天
- How soon? - Tomorrow.

137
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:10,240
我们会在这事上遭强烈抨击
We're gonna get hit hard on this.

138
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:11,810
总好过因为科里根的事被抨击
Better than getting hit on Corrigan.

139
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,200
你看《维埃拉秀》了吗
You saw Vieira?

140
00:07:13,730 --> 00:07:14,450
邓巴很聪明
Dunbar's smart.

141
00:07:14,450 --> 00:07:16,490
我们还没参选她就开始打压我们
She's running against us before we're even running.

142
00:07:16,510 --> 00:07:18,110
她也会在联邦应急管理署这事上攻击我们
She'll attack us on the FEMA thing, too.

143
00:07:18,110 --> 00:07:20,790
那就让她攻击  至少是我们控制舆论
Then let her. At least we're controlling the narrative.

144
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:23,170
我们第一次谈时  你说初秋
When we first spoke, you mentioned early fall.

145
00:07:23,170 --> 00:07:25,560
听着  邓巴势头强盛是因为没人挑战她
Look, Dunbar's got momentum because no one's challenging her.

146
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:27,050
但我们一宣布联邦应急管理署的计划
But once we drop the FEMA plan,

147
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:28,550
就会盖过她的报道
that'll take her off message.

148
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:31,530
然后你宣布参选就会分散她的注意  连环出击
And your candidacy will distract her. It's a one-two punch.

149
00:07:31,530 --> 00:07:33,100
我们会开始抢走女性选民的选票
We'll start bleeding away the woman's vote.

150
00:07:33,110 --> 00:07:35,500
我不确定现在几乎毫无准备
I'm just not sure how smart it is to rush into a campaign

151
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:37,330
-就宣布参选是否有利  -又不是真的参选
- with so little preparation. - This isn't a real campaign.

152
00:07:37,330 --> 00:07:39,200
但要看起来像真格的
But it needs to look like one.

153
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:42,560
我以为你想跟我一队呢
I thought you wanted to be on my ticket.

154
00:07:42,690 --> 00:07:44,680
我要赌上声誉
It's my reputation at stake.

155
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,850
-我不想看起来有勇无谋  -听着  没人...
- I don't want to look foolhardy. - Look, no one--

156
00:07:46,850 --> 00:07:48,280
市长明早将会宣布
Mayor's announcing in the morning.

157
00:07:48,280 --> 00:07:50,040
赛斯在跟他办公室合作
Seth's working with his office.

158
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,350
你看  杰姬  现在是最佳时机
You see, Jackie, this is perfect timing.

159
00:07:52,350 --> 00:07:53,830
联邦应急管理署计划开始实施
The FEMA plan goes into action,

160
00:07:53,830 --> 00:07:57,200
你几周后宣布参选  说你必须参选
you announce in a couple of weeks, you say you had to run.

161
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:59,540
安德伍德总统在联邦应急管理署恣意妄为
President Underwood is being reckless with FEMA.

162
00:07:59,540 --> 00:08:00,590
你出面反对我
You come out against me

163
00:08:00,590 --> 00:08:03,370
和《美国就业法案》  然后抢了邓巴的风头
and America Works and you steal Dunbar's thunder.

164
00:08:03,370 --> 00:08:04,760
之后等到我退出
And then I flip-flop

165
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:06,640
与你一同参选  不是态度大转弯吗
when I pull out and you put me on the ticket?

166
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:09,690
到那时候  五万人将拥有工作
By then, 50,000 people will have jobs,

167
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:11,160
那就不像是态度大转弯了
and it won't look like a flip-flop.

168
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:13,540
而是你豁然开朗
It'll look like you saw the light.

169
00:08:13,730 --> 00:08:15,400
听着  你跟雷米一起出去
Now, look, why don't you go off with Remy

170
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:16,630
讨论一下细节
and you discuss the details,

171
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:19,460
多考虑考虑再做决定
and just give it some thought before you decide.

172
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:23,530
-谢谢  总统先生  -来我办公室谈吧
- Thank you, Mr. President. - Let's talk in my office.

173
00:08:25,170 --> 00:08:26,950
我最大的担心是资金
My biggest concern is funding.

174
00:08:26,950 --> 00:08:28,780
我总不能坐普通舱去爱荷华
I couldn't fly coach to Iowa.

175
00:08:28,780 --> 00:08:30,300
我给你找一笔政治行动委员会资金来铺路
I'll get you some PAC money rolling your way.

176
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:32,060
应该足以让你启动宣传了
Should be enough to get you started.

177
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:36,440
如果我参选  就不能虎头蛇尾
If I run, it shouldn't be half-ass.

178
00:08:37,060 --> 00:08:39,580
所以我们得好好谈谈这个
Which is why we should talk about this.

179
00:08:45,350 --> 00:08:47,490
你想要有完整家庭的候选人
You want a candidate with a family.

180
00:08:48,010 --> 00:08:49,930
我们要抢的就是女性选民的选票
We are after the woman's vote.

181
00:08:52,230 --> 00:08:53,920
艾伦和我已经讨论过了
Alan and I have already talked about it.

182
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:56,380
是吗
You have?

183
00:08:57,880 --> 00:09:00,920
对  我们第一次约会时就开过结婚的玩笑
Yeah. We joked about getting married on our first date.

184
00:09:01,950 --> 00:09:04,710
我不用生产就能有两个孩子
I get two kids without the stretch marks.

185
00:09:08,330 --> 00:09:11,650
当我提到可能参选时  这就不再是玩笑话了
And when I mentioned I might run, it stopped becoming a joke.

186
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:13,890
艾伦能接受吗
Is Alan open to it?

187
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:17,500
-本就是他的主意  -那你呢
- It was his idea. - And what about you?

188
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:20,110
我们深爱彼此
We do love each other.

189
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:22,060
他看上去是个好人
He seems like a good guy.

190
00:09:22,060 --> 00:09:25,330
是的  他的孩子也很棒
He is. And his children are wonderful.

191
00:09:27,510 --> 00:09:29,180
你也应该考虑结婚
You should think about getting hitched.

192
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:34,060
我们要谈谈时间表吗
Should we talk timeline?

193
00:09:34,590 --> 00:09:37,240
-结婚的吗  -竞选
- For marriage? - The campaign.

194
00:09:50,220 --> 00:09:53,230
这可不是提议  这是会谈
This is far from an offer. This is a conversation.

195
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:55,560
而且是个从没发生过的会谈
And it's a conversation that never happened.

196
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:57,740
我从后门进来  待会儿还从后门离开
I took the back door in, I'll take the back door out.

197
00:09:57,740 --> 00:09:59,420
本季度工资单上没有你
We keep you off the payroll this quarter.

198
00:09:59,420 --> 00:10:01,540
你9月30日正式开始任职
You start officially September 30th.

199
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:04,310
下个季度的选举委员会文件才会有我  可以
Next quarter's FEC filings. It's fine.

200
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,380
关于工资你有什么想法
What are you thinking in terms of salary?

201
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,340
每季度2.2万
Twenty-two thousand per quarter.

202
00:10:10,060 --> 00:10:13,080
就算我这样  也不只值这个价
That's way below what I'm worth. Even in this state.

203
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,760
你觉得多少合适
What do you think's appropriate?

204
00:10:14,790 --> 00:10:16,920
25万加上3%的广告投入
Two-fifty and three points on the ad-buy.

205
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:19,700
-我们负担不起  -不  你们担得起
- That's beyond our means. - No, it's not.

206
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:21,730
这只是你财产的九牛一毛
It's a drop in the bucket from your estate.

207
00:10:21,730 --> 00:10:25,420
你说你想参加是因为你对这次竞选有信心
You said you wanted in because you believed in this campaign.

208
00:10:25,810 --> 00:10:28,480
-没错  -现在看来你是为了钱
- That's right. - Sounds like it's more about money.

209
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:32,360
我希望被重视  25万和少量广告投入并不多
It's about being valued. Two-fifty and the points is a bargain.

210
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:35,730
我想为你工作  而不是向你乞讨
I want to work for you, just not as a beggar.

211
00:10:35,730 --> 00:10:37,590
我们还不信任你  道格
We don't trust you yet, Doug.

212
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:41,440
可以说根本不信任你  所以你就是在乞讨
We don't even halfway trust you, so you are a beggar.

213
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:45,350
我还没证明自己  你也不应该信任我
And you shouldn't trust me... until I prove myself.

214
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:46,990
你不拿出筹码
That's a gamble you don't get to take

215
00:10:46,990 --> 00:10:48,730
就不能冒这个险
without putting chips on the table.

216
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:52,500
我和会辛西娅谈的
Cynthia and I will discuss.

217
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,130
感谢你抽空
Thank you for your time.

218
00:11:04,260 --> 00:11:05,430
我先看下外面
Let me check first.

219
00:11:08,410 --> 00:11:09,550
好了  安全
Okay, it's clear.

220
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:16,510
-你怎么看  -为什么要冒险
- What do you think? - Why take the gamble?

221
00:11:16,820 --> 00:11:18,430
我不想一开始决策
I don't want us to start making decisions

222
00:11:18,430 --> 00:11:20,770
就处于劣势  只会吃亏
from a position of weakness. That is how you lose.

223
00:11:20,770 --> 00:11:23,300
我觉得这是引狼入室
I think we're inviting the fox into the hen house.

224
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:24,580
要是间谍会
Anyone who wants to be a mole

225
00:11:24,580 --> 00:11:26,240
毫不犹豫地接受条件
accepts the first offer without question.

226
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:27,740
他却讨价还价
He's negotiating.

227
00:11:28,210 --> 00:11:29,750
所以你相信他了
So you actually believe him?

228
00:11:32,070 --> 00:11:33,500
半信半疑
Not necessarily.

229
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:38,990
但这不代表他没有价值
But that doesn't mean that he doesn't have value.

230
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:42,290
这些我们不需要了
Yeah, we're not gonna need any of these.

231
00:11:42,290 --> 00:11:43,710
全都放在这里
We're gonna keep these right here.

232
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:46,940
凯特·鲍德温  久仰久仰
Kate Baldwin, the one and only.

233
00:11:46,940 --> 00:11:48,640
我就说听到这里有人
I thought I heard somebody in here.

234
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:51,600
欢迎来白宫  或者应该说欢迎回白宫
Welcome to the White House. Or welcome back, I should say.

235
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:53,300
这里比我记忆中小
It feels smaller than I remember.

236
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:56,650
-他们安排你坐哪里  -这里  第二排
- Where do they have you sitting? - Right there, second row.

237
00:11:57,670 --> 00:11:59,870
我以为你会想要第一排
I would've thought you wanted first row.

238
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,700
我听说你说话会飞吐沫
I heard you spit when you talk.

239
00:12:02,350 --> 00:12:04,210
明天总统会讲什么
What's the president speaking about tomorrow?

240
00:12:04,230 --> 00:12:06,200
-你真是不浪费一分一秒  -没错
- You don't waste a minute, do you? - No.

241
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,630
实不相瞒  我很惊讶
I gotta say, I was surprised

242
00:12:07,630 --> 00:12:09,680
《电讯报》会派你来采访白宫
that the Telegraph sent you to cover the White House.

243
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:11,360
谁会离开伦敦分社啊
I mean, who leaves the London bureau?

244
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:13,220
艾拉是我的爱徒
Ayla was a protégée of mine.

245
00:12:13,410 --> 00:12:16,040
明白了  他们把老师父都请来了
I see, so now they bring in the big guns.

246
00:12:16,130 --> 00:12:17,940
就一位师父  资历也够老
Just one gun, but big enough.

247
00:12:17,940 --> 00:12:20,750
-别打我的主意  -什么主意
- Don't get any ideas. - About what?

248
00:12:21,050 --> 00:12:22,820
这个记者证我不会摘的
This is gonna stay around my neck.

249
00:12:22,970 --> 00:12:25,060
你不能连续解雇两个《电讯报》的记者
You can't boot two reporters in a row from the Telegraph.

250
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:28,270
-更不能是两个女记者  -我没这个意思
- Certainly not two women. - I have no desire to do that.

251
00:12:28,730 --> 00:12:30,390
跟你合作  我很荣幸
It's an honor to work with you.

252
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:31,890
普利策奖  皮博迪奖
Pulitzer, Peabody.

253
00:12:31,890 --> 00:12:33,540
再拿个诺贝尔奖  就是三料冠军了
Get yourself a Nobel, you'll have a trifecta.

254
00:12:33,540 --> 00:12:35,120
你可真会说话
Oh, you're almost charming.

255
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,980
凯特  我不是你的敌人
Kate, I'm not your enemy here.

256
00:12:36,980 --> 00:12:39,890
艾拉没做错  你却惩罚她
You punished Ayla for doing good work.

257
00:12:40,090 --> 00:12:41,910
她发力  你反击  很公平
She hit hard and you hit back. Fair enough.

258
00:12:41,910 --> 00:12:44,290
我会加倍发力
Well, I'm gonna hit twice as hard as she ever did

259
00:12:44,290 --> 00:12:46,560
因为我可以  也应该这么做
because I can and because someone should.

260
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,100
放马过来吧
I look forward to it.

261
00:12:50,780 --> 00:12:54,470
你真不会说谎  我们明早见
You're such a terrible liar. I'll see you bright and early.

262
00:12:56,190 --> 00:12:57,390
有时间吗
You got a minute?

263
00:12:58,570 --> 00:12:59,400
有
Sure.

264
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:05,690
这是明天声明的草稿
Here's the draft for the statement tomorrow.

265
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,680
想让你斧正一下
I want it to be perfect.

266
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,870
国会肯定会火力全开  回击我们
Congress will fire back, all guns blazing,

267
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:12,710
邓巴也肯定会大作文章
and I'm sure Dunbar will make a meal and a half out of it.

268
00:13:12,710 --> 00:13:17,010
但我觉得准备进攻的感觉很好
But I gotta say, I feel good. To be on the offensive.

269
00:13:17,010 --> 00:13:18,940
如果不能私下东拼西凑出这些钱来
If I can't scrape the money together behind the scenes,

270
00:13:18,940 --> 00:13:21,720
我就光天化日之下抢银行
I'll rob the bank in broad goddamn daylight.

271
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:25,570
我们要强行逼迫他们通过《美国就业法案》
We'll cram America Works down their throats and watch them choke.

272
00:13:25,570 --> 00:13:27,340
不再谨小慎微
Enough tiptoeing.

273
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:29,840
给
Here.

274
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:39,730
这些改动很棒
Oh, these changes are good.

275
00:13:41,290 --> 00:13:43,470
看你这么兴奋  我也很高兴
It makes me happy to see you excited.

276
00:13:43,540 --> 00:13:45,450
我又能松口气了
I feel free again.

277
00:13:47,350 --> 00:13:49,800
-真希望我也能  -还在忙决议案吗
- I wish I felt the same. - The resolution?

278
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:52,050
还有些最后的安抚工作  但...
Just some last minute hand-holding, but...

279
00:13:52,510 --> 00:13:53,660
我相信我们会成功的
I think we'll get there.

280
00:13:53,690 --> 00:13:56,410
我完全相信你
I have complete confidence in you.

281
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:03,020
-你喜欢这个房间吗  -还不错
- Do you like this room? - It's fine.

282
00:14:03,780 --> 00:14:06,080
我还没在这儿过过夜呢
You know, I haven't spent the night here yet.

283
00:14:08,010 --> 00:14:11,080
-也许我可以...  -我明早七点飞机
- Maybe I could-- - My plane leaves at seven.

284
00:14:11,210 --> 00:14:13,080
我得睡一会儿
I should probably get some sleep.

285
00:14:15,470 --> 00:14:17,600
明天记得看新闻  会很有意思的
You watch the news tomorrow. Should be fun.

286
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:20,420
-我会的  -晚安
- I will. - Good night.

287
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:20,710
17年  我在警局工作17年
Seventeen years, I served the Metro Police.

288
00:15:20,710 --> 00:15:23,330
我见过杀人抢劫
I've seen robberies and murders.

289
00:15:23,510 --> 00:15:25,350
见过毒品的瘟疫
I've seen the blight of drugs.

290
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:26,800
我见过小孩子
I've seen little kids

291
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:30,530
每天只能吃到从学校领到的那一顿饭
whose only meal each day was the one they get at school.

292
00:15:31,350 --> 00:15:32,870
知道这些事的根源是什么吗
You know what's at the root of all that?

293
00:15:33,230 --> 00:15:36,180
因为人们没有工作
Folks don't have jobs!

294
00:15:36,380 --> 00:15:39,820
华盛顿有六万失业人口
There are 60,000 unemployed people in Washington.

295
00:15:39,930 --> 00:15:41,480
这是场灾难
It's a disaster.

296
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:44,620
更丢脸的是  这是国家的首都
And it's a disgrace here in the nation's capital.

297
00:15:45,090 --> 00:15:47,340
所以今早  在总统的敦促下
So this morning, at the president's urging,

298
00:15:47,340 --> 00:15:52,510
我宣布哥伦比亚特区进入紧急状态
I am declaring a state of emergency in the District of Columbia.

299
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:55,820
并正式申请从联邦应急管理署赈灾基金
And I am formally requesting three billion dollars

300
00:15:55,820 --> 00:16:01,450
拨款30亿  用以安排人们重回岗位
from FEMA's Disaster Relief Fund to put people back to work.

301
00:16:01,450 --> 00:16:03,520
混帐东西
Motherfucker.

302
00:16:04,540 --> 00:16:06,540
任何人  真的是任何人
Anyone, and I mean anyone,

303
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:09,670
只要在哥伦比亚特区注册求职
who registers for work in the District of Columbia

304
00:16:09,940 --> 00:16:12,690
就保证可以得到工作
will be guaranteed a job.

305
00:16:12,690 --> 00:16:14,460
我在跟内阁努力增加
I'm working with my cabinet to increase

306
00:16:14,460 --> 00:16:18,250
基础设施建设  保养和修理方面的岗位
workforce devoted to infrastructure, maintenance and repair.

307
00:16:18,260 --> 00:16:19,360
国防部
The Defense Department

308
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:22,100
会增加探员招募和文职人员招聘
will ramp up recruitment and civilian employment.

309
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:26,290
任何雇佣《美就法》注册人员的私营企业
And any private sector companies who hire AmWorks registrants

310
00:16:26,290 --> 00:16:30,080
将得到每个岗位每年最高
will get up to $45,000 toward the yearly salary

311
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:32,000
4.5万美元的薪水补贴
of each job that they create.

312
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:35,520
我们的目标是12个月内全员就业
Our goal is full employment within twelve months.

313
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:38,520
我们希望华盛顿的成功
Our hope is that success in Washington

314
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:42,440
能说服国会在全国供资支持《美国就业法案》
will convince Congress to fund America Works nationwide.

315
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,020
现在  我会回答几个问题
Now, I'll take a few questions.

316
00:16:44,020 --> 00:16:46,040
总统先生
Mr. President!

317
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:55,440
大使女士  借一步说话
Madam Ambassador. A word, please.

318
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:56,890
失陪
Excuse me.

319
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:04,230
我们要收回对维和决议案的支持
We are withdrawing support of the peacekeeping resolution.

320
00:17:04,810 --> 00:17:07,010
-为什么  -因为以色列要收回
- Why? - Because Israel is.

321
00:17:07,470 --> 00:17:10,710
巴勒斯坦愿意接受计划  但不达成共识...
Palestine is open to the plan, but without consensus...

322
00:17:12,420 --> 00:17:14,430
这是直接来自耶路撒冷的意思吗
This came directly from Jerusalem?

323
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:17,140
-是的  外交部长  -伊莉安娜说什么了吗
- Yes, the foreign minister. - Nothing came from Eliana?

324
00:17:17,150 --> 00:17:18,960
没有  但我是来找她谈的
No, but I came to speak to her.

325
00:17:21,630 --> 00:17:23,360
我会亲自跟她谈  谢谢你  哈桑
I'll speak to her myself. Thank you, Hasan.

326
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:24,650
谢谢你  大使
Thank you, Ambassador.

327
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:39,120
莫斯科威胁说要卖武器给伊朗
Moscow is threatening to sell arms to Iran.

328
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,070
他们时常这么威胁
They always make that threat.

329
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:43,000
耶路撒冷方面认为这个决议案
The feeling in Jerusalem is that this resolution

330
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,150
也许会逼他们铤而走险  不值得冒险
may push them over the edge. It's not worth the risk.

331
00:17:45,150 --> 00:17:47,800
你为什么不来找我  还有两小时就要投票了
Why didn't you come to me? The vote's in two hours.

332
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,620
我30分钟前刚接到电话
I got the call 30 minutes ago.

333
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:51,320
俄罗斯不想丢面子
Russia doesn't want to be humiliated

334
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:52,590
因为我们绕过了他们
because we did this without them.

335
00:17:52,590 --> 00:17:54,580
你知道他们就是虚张声势
You know it's a bluff on their part.

336
00:17:54,610 --> 00:17:58,010
总理认为这次投票只是象征性的
The prime minister feels that this vote is just symbolic.

337
00:17:58,290 --> 00:18:00,350
美国不会真的出动军队
That the US won't actually contribute troops.

338
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:03,570
不  一旦通过  我们绝对会坚持到底
No, we will absolutely follow through once it's passed.

339
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:05,660
总理有疑虑
The prime minister has his doubts.

340
00:18:07,130 --> 00:18:08,780
抱歉  这不是我能控制的
I'm sorry, it's out of my hands.

341
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:11,370
克莱尔
Claire?

342
00:18:13,080 --> 00:18:16,180
各位大使  我需要你们撤回决议案
Ambassadors, I need you to withdraw the resolution.

343
00:18:16,180 --> 00:18:17,520
我们不能达成共识
We lost consensus.

344
00:18:17,520 --> 00:18:20,060
我需要推迟投票  直到我们重新达成共识
I need to postpone the vote until we get it back.

345
00:18:23,130 --> 00:18:25,840
特拉弗斯部长是个很好的例子
Secretary Travers is a good example.

346
00:18:26,450 --> 00:18:27,700
国土安全部
Homeland Security?

347
00:18:28,010 --> 00:18:31,060
-应该说是前部长  -他下台了吗
- Former secretary, I should say. - He's done?

348
00:18:31,290 --> 00:18:33,620
还没宣布  但史蒂夫打电话给我了
They haven't announced, but Steve called me.

349
00:18:33,870 --> 00:18:37,150
说他在联邦应急管理署的事上反对总统
Said he stood up to the president on this FEMA nonsense.

350
00:18:37,490 --> 00:18:40,060
国土安全部对联邦应急管理署有管辖权
Homeland Security has jurisdiction over FEMA now.

351
00:18:40,070 --> 00:18:40,860
没错
Right.

352
00:18:40,950 --> 00:18:44,880
总统当场要求他提交辞呈
The president demanded his letter of resignation right then and there.

353
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:48,640
-这些都是非正式对话  -明白
- This is all off the record. - Yeah.

354
00:18:49,780 --> 00:18:53,050
-保罗真是个大嘴巴  -所以是真的吗
- Paul's got a big mouth. - So it's true?

355
00:18:53,310 --> 00:18:55,630
-这是非正式对话吗  -绝对是
- This is off the record? - Completely.

356
00:18:55,910 --> 00:18:57,340
我用加密电话给你打
Let me call you on my encrypted phone.

357
00:18:57,350 --> 00:18:58,550
我的号码有屏蔽  所以...
My number is blocked, so--

358
00:18:58,550 --> 00:19:01,020
这里是国土安全部  我有你电话
This is Homeland Security. I have your number.

359
00:19:07,740 --> 00:19:10,320
有电话呼入  按接听键...
Incoming call. Press the pickup bu--

360
00:19:10,780 --> 00:19:14,100
-部长先生  -是真的  我辞职了
- Mr. Secretary. - It's true. I resigned.

361
00:19:14,690 --> 00:19:16,450
那你为什么还在办公室
Why are you still in the office?

362
00:19:16,450 --> 00:19:19,020
点卯撞钟等白宫公布
Punching the clock until the White House wants to go public.

363
00:19:19,020 --> 00:19:20,330
如果你反对那项政策
Why wouldn't you go public yourself,

364
00:19:20,330 --> 00:19:21,990
为什么不自己公布消息
if you're so against the policy?

365
00:19:21,990 --> 00:19:23,840
我是为总统服务的
I serve at the pleasure of the president.

366
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:25,460
兰德里已经提供了信息
I have Landry on background.

367
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,720
我要写关于辞职的报道
I'm writing about the resignation.

368
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:30,780
我无法阻止你  但你不能引用我的话
And I can't stop you. But there won't be a quote from me.

369
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:35,290
别让政府逃脱责任
Don't let the administration off the hook.

370
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,870
这是发表反对意见的机会
This an opportunity to speak out.

371
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:39,490
能做到我这一步
You don't have the career I've had

372
00:19:39,490 --> 00:19:42,050
不是靠公开批评上司
by criticizing your bosses publicly,

373
00:19:42,050 --> 00:19:43,890
不管你觉得自己多厉害
no matter how strongly you feel.

374
00:19:44,890 --> 00:19:46,670
和联邦应急管理署的署长阿尼·希尔瓦谈谈
Talk to Arnie Silva, the FEMA Administrator.

375
00:19:46,670 --> 00:19:49,140
他比我更反感这一切
He's more disgusted by all this than I am.

376
00:20:15,690 --> 00:20:19,630
事关人命  他却不管不顾
People's lives are in the balance. And he doesn't care.

377
00:20:23,210 --> 00:20:25,590
这是我们接下来12个月的预测
Our projections for the next 12 months.

378
00:20:27,180 --> 00:20:28,260
我们正处于拉尼娜时期
We're in a La Niña phase,

379
00:20:28,270 --> 00:20:31,060
也就是说太平洋温度下降
which means falling temperatures in the Pacific.

380
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:34,300
我们预计这一季至少要发生两次大型山体滑坡
We expect at least two major landfalls this season.

381
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,350
家园被毁  损失数十亿
Homes destroyed, billions in damage,

382
00:20:36,350 --> 00:20:38,520
成千上万人断电
tens of thousands without power.

383
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,420
这还仅仅是飓风的危害  要是碰上大地震
And that's just hurricanes. If we get a major earthquake,

384
00:20:41,420 --> 00:20:43,170
或者洪水  再或森林火灾
or flood, or forest fire...

385
00:20:45,580 --> 00:20:46,680
都在这里面了
It's all in there.

386
00:20:48,070 --> 00:20:49,570
他曾要求你辞职吗
Has he asked you to resign?

387
00:20:49,650 --> 00:20:50,720
他威胁过我
He threatened it.

388
00:20:52,020 --> 00:20:53,680
但是我说我会配合
But I said I'd cooperate.

389
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,310
为什么
Why?

390
00:20:56,760 --> 00:20:58,650
没人比我更有经验
Nobody has more experience.

391
00:20:59,810 --> 00:21:02,100
如果离开  我无法原谅自己
I couldn't forgive myself if I left.

392
00:21:02,150 --> 00:21:04,190
但是你刚才不是说  如果赈灾基金耗尽
But you just said, if the Relief Fund is depleted, then--

393
00:21:04,190 --> 00:21:05,600
那人们会受难
People will suffer.

394
00:21:07,580 --> 00:21:11,520
但在我的照管下  受难的人能少些
But on my watch, fewer will suffer.

395
00:21:12,460 --> 00:21:14,080
我需要引用你的话  希尔瓦先生
I need a quote, Mr. Silva.

396
00:21:15,140 --> 00:21:16,260
我做不到
I can't do that.

397
00:21:16,690 --> 00:21:19,010
人命关天  你有责任
People could die, you have a responsibility.

398
00:21:19,390 --> 00:21:22,350
总统创建了一种噤声与恐惧交织的氛围
The president has built a culture of silence and fear.

399
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:24,250
你可以结束它
That can end with you.

400
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:29,680
这个文件夹比任何话语都更有说服力
That folder will speak louder than anything I could say.

401
00:21:30,130 --> 00:21:33,210
{\pos(271.2,96.3)}华尔街电讯报

402
00:21:30,130 --> 00:21:33,210
{\pos(198.6,103.05)}联邦应急管理署遭劫
民众付出代价

403
00:21:30,130 --> 00:21:33,210
{\pos(256.5,168.3)}总统解雇国防部长

404
00:21:34,580 --> 00:21:38,490
同一天头版两篇报道都出自鲍德温女士吗
Two front page bylines on the same day for Ms. Baldwin?

405
00:21:38,490 --> 00:21:41,050
真是踢走只斗狗  放进条火龙来
You kicked out a pit bull and you let in a dragon.

406
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:43,310
我没想到《电讯报》能再派一个她这样的
I didn't think the Telegraph would send someone like her.

407
00:21:43,310 --> 00:21:45,310
也许你是根本没考虑
Well, maybe you just didn't think.

408
00:21:45,790 --> 00:21:47,390
您让我管束他们  先生
You wanted me to implement discipline, sir.

409
00:21:47,390 --> 00:21:49,240
传递讯息  我做了
To send a message. And so I did.

410
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:52,230
他们的回应更强烈  是不是
Well, they've sent back an even stronger message, haven't they?

411
00:21:52,230 --> 00:21:53,950
我对此负责  先生
I take responsibility for that, sir,

412
00:21:53,950 --> 00:21:55,930
我会不遗余力让她听话的
and I will do my best to keep her in line.

413
00:21:55,930 --> 00:21:57,530
不遗余力
Your best?

414
00:21:57,960 --> 00:22:00,480
有他们总编辑保着  谁也碰不了她
It's their top bureau chief. She's untouchable.

415
00:22:00,530 --> 00:22:03,410
我不想假装我能百分之百控制她
I don't want to pretend that I can control her 100 percent.

416
00:22:03,710 --> 00:22:05,620
-特拉弗斯  -他否认曾与她谈话
- Travers? - Denied speaking with her,

417
00:22:05,620 --> 00:22:06,930
但是肯定是他
but it must be him.

418
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:08,900
我想内阁中再没别人会了
I don't think anybody else in the cabinet would.

419
00:22:08,910 --> 00:22:10,340
我们确认他辞职一事
Let's confirm his resignation.

420
00:22:10,350 --> 00:22:12,260
现在还保密没意义了
No point in keeping it a secret now.

421
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:14,090
告诉史蒂夫他可以把办公室清空了
Tell Steve he can vacate his office.

422
00:22:14,090 --> 00:22:15,380
那希尔瓦呢
And what about Silva?

423
00:22:15,720 --> 00:22:18,350
关于防灾预测的细节相当专业
The details on the disaster projections are very inside baseball.

424
00:22:18,350 --> 00:22:20,960
我们不能炒了他  如果飓风来了
We can't fire him! If there's a hurricane,

425
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:23,990
他是唯一能防止灾难变成浩劫的人
he's the only guy that can keep a disaster from becoming a catastrophe.

426
00:22:23,990 --> 00:22:26,820
-邓巴说什么  -还没有公开表示
- And what's Dunbar saying? - Nothing yet, publicly.

427
00:22:26,820 --> 00:22:28,510
她可能想让好戏演到终场
She's probably letting this play out.

428
00:22:28,510 --> 00:22:30,710
让我自掘坟墓
Letting me dig my own grave.

429
00:22:32,850 --> 00:22:35,720
我们必须推销《美国就业法案》
We have to sell America Works.

430
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:37,550
等人们有工作  就不需要别的吹捧了
It should sell itself once we get people employed.

431
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:40,060
是要这效果  但我们不能止步于此
Well, that's the idea, but we don't stop there.

432
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:42,610
-广告和公告牌  -用谁的钱
- Commercials and billboards? - On whose money?

433
00:22:43,630 --> 00:22:45,480
即使这样  广告也不够
And even so, we need more than ad-buys.

434
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:49,720
我们需要...挖掘它背后的深意
We need... We need the philosophy behind it.

435
00:22:49,730 --> 00:22:52,960
我们需要实质性的东西  我们需要...
We need something of substance. We need something...

436
00:23:04,340 --> 00:23:08,500
我们需要能启发想象力的东西
We need something that will capture the imagination.

437
00:23:09,950 --> 00:23:11,890
-你们玩《纪念碑谷》吗  -那是什么
- Either of you play Monument Valley? - What's that?

438
00:23:11,890 --> 00:23:13,740
-是一款游戏  -我不玩游戏  先生
- It's a video game. - I don't play them, sir.

439
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:15,990
我在易趣上把Xbox卖了  玩着太上瘾
I sold my Xbox on eBay. It was too addictive.

440
00:23:15,990 --> 00:23:17,740
不  不是主机游戏
No, it's not a console game.

441
00:23:18,150 --> 00:23:19,050
你们读读这个
You both read this

442
00:23:19,050 --> 00:23:21,500
然后告诉我你不想玩这个
and then tell me that you wouldn't want to play this.

443
00:23:25,470 --> 00:23:27,070
我敢说全国只有九个顾问
I'd say there's nine consultants in the country

444
00:23:27,070 --> 00:23:28,560
真正懂得外交政策
who truly know foreign policy.

445
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:30,440
我是第一
Me, I'm number one.

446
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:32,520
失去意识的我是第二
Me in a coma is number two.

447
00:23:32,710 --> 00:23:34,680
但是还剩下七个逊于我的呢
But that still leaves seven who are cheaper.

448
00:23:34,690 --> 00:23:36,040
我重视良言
I value good counsel,

449
00:23:36,140 --> 00:23:38,670
我也有足够脑子知道自己的欠缺
and I'm smart enough to know what I don't know.

450
00:23:38,670 --> 00:23:40,590
截至目前你对我们的评价如何
What would be your assessment of us so far?

451
00:23:40,590 --> 00:23:42,610
迈克尔·科里根的事你处理得一团糟
You're making a big stink out of this Michael Corrigan thing,

452
00:23:42,610 --> 00:23:44,160
但这还只是表面上的
but that's just surface.

453
00:23:44,290 --> 00:23:46,630
你得明白科里根为何被捕
You have to understand why Corrigan got arrested.

454
00:23:46,630 --> 00:23:48,840
佩特罗夫想迎合传统观念人群
Petrov's appealing to his traditional base.

455
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:52,240
不  这与约旦河谷有关
No. This is about the Jordan Valley.

456
00:23:52,420 --> 00:23:53,670
我不太明白
I don't follow.

457
00:23:54,540 --> 00:23:55,570
复仇
Retaliation.

458
00:23:55,810 --> 00:23:57,580
这得回溯到几个月前的峰会上
It goes back to the summit a couple of months ago.

459
00:23:57,580 --> 00:24:02,410
这里是约旦河谷
Look, this... is the Jordan Valley.

460
00:24:04,760 --> 00:24:06,480
等一下  我放到大屏幕上去
All right, hold on, I'll make it easier.

461
00:24:12,670 --> 00:24:14,770
这是河谷  在这里
That's the Valley. Right there.

462
00:24:14,860 --> 00:24:16,950
1967年以来一直归以色列
Occupied by Israel since 1967,

463
00:24:16,950 --> 00:24:20,000
一直是与巴勒斯坦达成和平协定的拦路虎
it's been a major roadblock in any peace accord with the Palestinians.

464
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,840
安德伍德派维和部队过去  以色列人走了
Underwood sends peacekeeping troops, the Israelis leave,

465
00:24:22,840 --> 00:24:25,700
-巴勒斯坦人开心了  -没那么简单
- the Palestinians are happy. - It's not that simple.

466
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:28,420
所有人都为这个小地方牵肠挂肚
Everyone gets hung up on this little patch of land ten miles by 40,

467
00:24:28,420 --> 00:24:29,740
但你得往远了看
but you have to look outwards,

468
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:32,180
越过约旦  叙利亚还有伊拉克
past Jordan and Syria, past Iraq.

469
00:24:32,180 --> 00:24:36,070
这里  高加索山脉
Here... to the Caucasus.

470
00:24:36,390 --> 00:24:37,900
这里是俄罗斯的地盘
That's Russia's sphere of influence.

471
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:40,480
他们不觉得维和部队是中东问题
They don't see the peacekeeping force as a Middle East issue.

472
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:42,640
而是觉得这是美国军队的战略调度
They see it as strategic deployment of US troops

473
00:24:42,640 --> 00:24:44,580
离他们南部边界不到一千里
less than a thousand miles from their southern border.

474
00:24:44,580 --> 00:24:47,600
你是说  科里根只是一枚棋子  一个筹码
So you're saying Corrigan's a pawn, a play for leverage?

475
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:49,240
更像是打响的第一枪
More of a first salvo.

476
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:52,220
莫斯科要表明对反抗决议案的决心
Moscow wants to show it's serious about fighting this resolution.

477
00:24:52,390 --> 00:24:53,780
要我猜的话
Now, if I had to guess,

478
00:24:54,410 --> 00:24:56,630
安德伍德在峰会时本想拉拢俄罗斯
Underwood tried to bring Russia into the mix during the summit.

479
00:24:56,630 --> 00:24:58,800
成为合作伙伴
Get involved early on as partners.

480
00:24:58,990 --> 00:25:00,570
但佩特罗夫不肯合作
And when Petrov didn't play ball,

481
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:04,190
安德伍德就转守为攻  是场豪赌
Underwood went on the offensive, which is a huge gamble.

482
00:25:04,660 --> 00:25:06,980
-怎么说  -没人想让联合国军队过去
- Tell me how. - Nobody wants UN troops there.

483
00:25:06,980 --> 00:25:08,660
以色列人不想  巴勒斯坦人不想
Not the Israelis, not the Palestinians,

484
00:25:08,660 --> 00:25:09,670
阿拉伯人也不想
not the Arabs.

485
00:25:09,670 --> 00:25:12,100
他们合作都是因为美国的施压
They're playing along because the US is pressuring them.

486
00:25:12,590 --> 00:25:14,640
但只要有一点差错
But just one little thing needs to go wrong,

487
00:25:14,780 --> 00:25:17,440
所有人都拿着火柴等着点你的炸药包
and you've got a tinderbox where everyone's holding matches.

488
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:20,910
那他为什么要采取这样的行动
So why is he following this course of action at all?

489
00:25:21,390 --> 00:25:22,550
因为他很聪明
Because he's smart.

490
00:25:23,070 --> 00:25:25,180
-可你刚说  -他是聪明过头
- You just said-- - He's being too smart.

491
00:25:25,410 --> 00:25:28,970
要是这招行得通  他能拿诺贝尔奖
If it pays off, hey, he wins a Nobel Prize. But...

492
00:25:30,750 --> 00:25:34,610
但行不通的话  他毫无反击之力
if it backfires, he leaves himself wide open.

493
00:25:34,710 --> 00:25:36,670
到时你得火力全开抨击他
And that's when you need to hit him hard.

494
00:25:36,850 --> 00:25:39,550
一项让世界更为危险的灾难性外交政策
A disastrous foreign policy that made the world more dangerous.

495
00:25:39,550 --> 00:25:42,070
他还让他毫无外交经验的妻子
And he had his wife with zero foreign policy experience

496
00:25:42,070 --> 00:25:45,380
-主掌大局  -我想让你加入  乔
- lead the goddamn charge. - I'd like to bring you aboard, Joe.

497
00:25:45,380 --> 00:25:47,930
-你什么时候能开工  -我已经开工了
- When can you start? - I believe I already did.

498
00:25:47,930 --> 00:25:49,790
我今天稍后会把文件给你拿来
I'll get the paperwork over to you later today.

499
00:25:49,790 --> 00:25:51,670
我想问下  是谁推荐的我
Let me ask, who referred me?

500
00:25:51,670 --> 00:25:54,700
-你声名在外  -是啊  声名在外的混蛋
- You have quite a reputation. - Yeah, for being an asshole.

501
00:25:54,780 --> 00:25:56,780
肯定是你尊敬的人大力举荐了我
Somebody you respect must have recommended me highly.

502
00:25:56,780 --> 00:25:58,760
安德伍德的前雇员
A former Underwood staffer.

503
00:25:59,030 --> 00:26:00,300
我没跟他的人共事过
I never worked with any of his people.

504
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:02,880
这也是他举荐你的原因之一
Which is one of the reasons he recommended you.

505
00:26:03,050 --> 00:26:04,010
有道理
Touché.

506
00:26:07,980 --> 00:26:08,980
这是什么
What is this?

507
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:11,480
如果你们卖给伊朗一丁点武器
A list of the Russian officials who will be sanctioned

508
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:14,500
就将遭制裁的俄国官员名单
if you sell a single truckload of arms to Iran.

509
00:26:14,770 --> 00:26:16,630
我都没进前十
I didn't even make the top ten.

510
00:26:16,950 --> 00:26:19,560
制裁会进一步扩大
These sanctions can and will escalate.

511
00:26:19,740 --> 00:26:20,770
然后呢
And then what?

512
00:26:20,770 --> 00:26:23,860
我们联合起来  实现对他们的制裁
We'd build a coalition to impose their own sanctions.

513
00:26:23,860 --> 00:26:24,960
然后呢
And then what?

514
00:26:25,190 --> 00:26:25,990
亚历克西
Alexi,

515
00:26:26,780 --> 00:26:30,090
你明白这会在俄罗斯造成怎样的金融危机
you know what an economic crisis that would be for Russia.

516
00:26:30,580 --> 00:26:32,890
就如你们和中国打的贸易战一样吗
Like the trade war you waged with China?

517
00:26:32,980 --> 00:26:36,370
只不过我们只有3%的出口额是给美国
Except in our case, only three percent of exports go to the US.

518
00:26:36,370 --> 00:26:38,670
欧洲需要我们的天然气
And Europe needs our natural gas.

519
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:41,950
他们不会为几个给伊朗的短程导弹放弃这些
They won't forfeit that over a few short-range missiles to Iran.

520
00:26:41,950 --> 00:26:43,400
你不会想在恐怖主义国家军备
You don't want to challenge us

521
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:45,420
这种问题上挑战我们
on the armament of a terrorist state.

522
00:26:45,420 --> 00:26:47,670
我们永远不会出现这种问题
We'll never be presented with that problem.

523
00:26:47,670 --> 00:26:49,670
你无法向以色列人保证出军
You can't assure the Israelis you'll provide troops.

524
00:26:49,670 --> 00:26:52,870
国会两党都不支持总统
The President doesn't have the support of either party in Congress.

525
00:26:53,210 --> 00:26:54,340
不出兵就没有以色列支持
No troops, no Israel.

526
00:26:54,340 --> 00:26:55,880
没有以色列支持就没有共识
No Israel, no consensus.

527
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:58,850
没有共识  决议案就没戏
No consensus, no resolution.

528
00:27:00,810 --> 00:27:02,920
我会让决议案通过的
I will get this resolution passed.

529
00:27:03,210 --> 00:27:06,740
不要小瞧我的能力和决心
Don't underestimate my ability or desire to do so.

530
00:27:07,220 --> 00:27:09,630
我放任你的热情够久了
I've indulged your enthusiasm long enough.

531
00:27:09,630 --> 00:27:11,370
你有点好高鹜远啊  克莱尔
You've bit off more than you can chew, Claire.

532
00:27:11,370 --> 00:27:12,820
交给专业人士来处理
Leave this to the professionals

533
00:27:12,820 --> 00:27:15,870
你的决议案也能死得痛快点
and let your little resolution die a painless death.

534
00:27:16,050 --> 00:27:18,730
事实就是  你不是当大使的料
The truth is, you have no business being ambassador

535
00:27:18,730 --> 00:27:20,900
就跟我不是当第一夫人的料一样
any more than I do being First Lady.

536
00:27:29,320 --> 00:27:31,230
裙子不错
That's a very nice dress, by the way.

537
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:37,140
"她用扫帚捅地板
"She stabbed the floor with a broom.

538
00:27:37,420 --> 00:27:40,200
每周三卡拉OK之夜
Karaoke every Wednesday.

539
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:44,970
会有音痴的醉妞唱毁小甜甜的歌
Some tone-deaf drunk girl mutilating Britney Spears.

540
00:27:45,230 --> 00:27:47,860
她知道楼下酒吧听不到楼上捅扫帚的声音
She knew they couldn't hear the broom in the bar below.

541
00:27:48,010 --> 00:27:52,150
但我们都需要一种形式  而这是她的
But we all need a ritual, and this was hers.

542
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:54,070
捅三下  木头对木头
Three short thrusts, wood on wood,

543
00:27:54,070 --> 00:27:57,610
完全没有作用的空洞之声
a hollow sound which accomplished nothing.

544
00:27:57,910 --> 00:27:59,640
戴维马上就回家了
David would be home soon.

545
00:27:59,970 --> 00:28:02,790
他会说  '太热了'  她打开了窗户
'It's too hot,' he'd say. She opened the window.

546
00:28:03,390 --> 00:28:07,140
音乐非常大声  她无法忽略"
The music was so loud, she couldn't ignore it."

547
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:19,790
给你
Here.

548
00:28:23,510 --> 00:28:24,510
你不买新的吗
Aren't you gonna buy the new one?

549
00:28:24,510 --> 00:28:27,360
我会买电子书  但你能在这本上签字吗
I will, on my Kindle. But will you please sign this?

550
00:28:28,540 --> 00:28:32,050
-写给谁  -莱斯莉  LESLEY
- Who should I make it out to? - Lesley. L-E-S-L-E-Y.

551
00:28:32,880 --> 00:28:34,970
《天蝎》改变了我的生活
Scorpio totally changed my life.

552
00:28:34,970 --> 00:28:38,790
那种力量  愤怒  是你的书里我最喜欢的
The energy and the anger... It's my favorite book of yours.

553
00:28:38,900 --> 00:28:40,930
大概是我最喜欢的书了
Probably my favorite book, period.

554
00:28:42,760 --> 00:28:44,750
-一定要读新的  -好的
- Make sure you read the new one. - Yes.

555
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,470
要写给谁呢
Who should I make it out to?

556
00:28:51,070 --> 00:28:52,690
{\pos(203.1,207)}雷米·丹顿  白宫幕僚长

557
00:28:58,390 --> 00:29:00,810
这是对《斯塔福法案》的曲解  你心里清楚
It's a perversion of the Stafford Act and you know it.

558
00:29:00,820 --> 00:29:03,930
这对《斯塔福法案》的解读  我们的解读不同
It's a reading of the Stafford Act. We read it differently.

559
00:29:03,930 --> 00:29:05,400
你不能占用
You can't just raid funds

560
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:07,790
国会调拨用于特定用途的资金
that Congress appropriated for a specific use,

561
00:29:07,790 --> 00:29:10,440
-任意按你的想法使用  -显然我可以
- then use them however you want. - Clearly, I can.

562
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:12,980
这是在直接挑衅国会  总统先生
This is a direct challenge to Congress, Mr. President.

563
00:29:13,010 --> 00:29:13,750
鲍勃和我已经同意
Bob and I have agreed.

564
00:29:13,750 --> 00:29:15,720
两党都会在这个问题上反对你
Both parties will fight you on this.

565
00:29:15,980 --> 00:29:18,620
那至少我促进了两党合作
Well, at least I'm cultivating bipartisanship.

566
00:29:18,670 --> 00:29:20,510
先生们  我不想这样做
Gentlemen, I don't want to do this,

567
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:22,370
但你们给我留了什么选择余地吗
but what choice have you left me?

568
00:29:22,370 --> 00:29:24,520
我们立法部门就是要审核你的行政部门
Our branch is here to check yours.

569
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:25,610
如果我们认为《美国就业法案》
If we didn't feel America Works

570
00:29:25,610 --> 00:29:26,660
不配使用纳税人的钱
warranted taxpayer money,

571
00:29:26,660 --> 00:29:29,330
-那就不能立法  -听我说
- then it's not fit to be law. - Now, look.

572
00:29:29,330 --> 00:29:31,730
这是两党领导人第一次一起
This is the first time that the leaders of both parties

573
00:29:31,730 --> 00:29:33,250
跟我同处一室会面
have met with me in one room,

574
00:29:33,250 --> 00:29:35,830
而且不是因为我没邀请过你们  是你们拒绝了
and not because I didn't invite you, because you declined.

575
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:38,820
既然我们都在这里  那就充分利用这次机会
So, now that we're here, let's make the most of it.

576
00:29:38,820 --> 00:29:40,510
我愿意在联邦应急管理署方面让步
I'm willing to walk back on FEMA

577
00:29:40,510 --> 00:29:42,860
前提是让《美就法》进入国会投票
if we can discuss putting AmWorks on the floor.

578
00:29:42,860 --> 00:29:44,470
你们在教育法案上威逼过我们
You bullied us on the Education Bill.

579
00:29:44,470 --> 00:29:45,450
还有政府停摆
And the government freeze.

580
00:29:45,450 --> 00:29:46,940
这次不会成功的
It's not gonna work this time.

581
00:29:46,940 --> 00:29:49,560
等它成功了  你再说这话吧
You watch it work and then tell me it didn't.

582
00:29:49,570 --> 00:29:52,440
我们要起草法律  说这样使用赈灾基金是违法的
We're drafting a law, saying this use of the DRF is illegal.

583
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:54,580
谁来执行这项法律
And who's going to enforce that law?

584
00:29:54,580 --> 00:29:56,570
我们曾准备弹劾一位总统
We were ready to impeach one president.

585
00:29:56,570 --> 00:29:59,410
如果有必要  也会对你采取相同措施
We'll do the same with you if necessary.

586
00:29:59,540 --> 00:30:01,710
然后让唐纳德·布莱斯坐进这间办公室吗
And put Donald Blythe in this office?

587
00:30:01,710 --> 00:30:03,490
你们也知道他干不了这份工作
You know he's not up for the job.

588
00:30:03,490 --> 00:30:06,290
国会会因为失职而被抨击
Congress would get killed for malpractice.

589
00:30:06,340 --> 00:30:07,960
不管你们认为我多狡诈
As crooked as you may think I am,

590
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:10,840
你们清楚我可以顶住压力  而唐纳德不行
you know I can handle the pressure, and you know Donald can't.

591
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:12,660
你们通过法律吧  我会否决的
So pass your law, I'll veto it.

592
00:30:12,660 --> 00:30:14,370
等你们在参议院推翻我
And when you overrule me in the Senate,

593
00:30:14,370 --> 00:30:16,600
我们就让法庭裁决吧
we'll let the third branch decide.

594
00:30:16,890 --> 00:30:19,060
别向国会宣战  总统先生
Don't declare war on Congress, Mr. President.

595
00:30:19,070 --> 00:30:22,160
不是向国会宣战  我是向衰退宣战
Not on Congress. I'm declaring war on atrophy.

596
00:30:22,790 --> 00:30:24,990
但如今谁又能看出区别呢
But these days, who could tell the difference?

597
00:31:24,260 --> 00:31:25,530
不如这样
So how about this?

598
00:31:28,320 --> 00:31:29,710
我叫份披萨
I'll order a pizza.

599
00:31:30,770 --> 00:31:33,140
到了之后  我拿进这个房间
When it gets here, I bring it into this room...

600
00:31:34,410 --> 00:31:36,680
手臂上搭一条纸巾
with a paper towel draped over my arm.

601
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:39,900
来了  就像客房服务
Voilà. Just like... room service.

602
00:31:40,820 --> 00:31:42,830
你不让你的孩子吃披萨
You don't let your kids eat pizza.

603
00:31:43,290 --> 00:31:45,700
因为我见识过那对颈动脉的危害
Well, because I've seen what it does to a carotid artery.

604
00:31:47,220 --> 00:31:48,500
而且你又不是我的孩子
And you're not my kids.

605
00:31:52,870 --> 00:31:54,350
你觉得他们喜欢我吗
Do you think they like me?

606
00:31:58,120 --> 00:31:59,240
他们崇拜你
They adore you.

607
00:32:00,940 --> 00:32:03,610
马特问你能不能教他开车
Matt asked if you could teach him how to drive.

608
00:32:03,610 --> 00:32:04,720
-真的吗  -嗯
- Really? - Yeah.

609
00:32:04,720 --> 00:32:06,650
他说你不会那么苛刻
He says you'd be less judgmental.

610
00:32:13,050 --> 00:32:14,370
你想结婚吗
Do you want to get married?

611
00:32:19,110 --> 00:32:20,550
跟你还是笼统来说
To you, or in general?

612
00:32:24,470 --> 00:32:25,740
我是认真的
I'm serious.

613
00:32:29,670 --> 00:32:31,010
从哪冒出的想法
So where'd this come from?

614
00:32:32,330 --> 00:32:33,610
我们都谈过了
We've talked about it.

615
00:32:35,100 --> 00:32:37,340
我们说"我爱你"
We say "I love you."

616
00:32:38,490 --> 00:32:41,270
我想要个丈夫  你想要个妻子
I want a husband. You want a wife.

617
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:46,270
我们俩挺合适  你不觉得吗
This works, the two of us, don't you think?

618
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:51,650
-非常浪漫  -我们不是浪漫过了吗
- It's very romantic. - Aren't we past romance?

619
00:32:51,810 --> 00:32:53,020
我给你卖了个戒指
I bought you a ring.

620
00:32:56,160 --> 00:32:57,920
你为什么都没说
Why didn't you say anything?

621
00:32:58,710 --> 00:33:00,320
不然怎么是惊喜
It's the element of surprise.

622
00:33:01,110 --> 00:33:02,580
不就是要有惊喜吗
That's kind of the point, isn't it?

623
00:33:04,140 --> 00:33:06,750
在我的储物箱里  你想要的话我去拿
It's in my glove compartment. I can go get it if you want.

624
00:33:08,740 --> 00:33:11,190
不  我要你定披萨
No, I want you to order the pizza.

625
00:33:13,740 --> 00:33:15,610
明天再弄戒指的事
We can do the whole ring thing tomorrow.

626
00:33:35,580 --> 00:33:36,820
你什么时候回来的
When did you get in?

627
00:33:37,350 --> 00:33:40,080
-几小时前  -过来坐吧
- Couple of hours ago. - Well, come and sit down.

628
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:43,380
我觉得我好像有三天没见到你了
I feel like I haven't seen you for what, has it been three days?

629
00:33:43,380 --> 00:33:44,830
应该是四天
Four, I think.

630
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:47,650
都记不清了
It's just all been a big blur.

631
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:49,650
我在纽约也一样
Same in New York.

632
00:33:49,670 --> 00:33:50,620
有好消息吗
Any luck?

633
00:33:50,940 --> 00:33:53,080
他们跟复读机似的  弗兰西斯
They're like a broken record, Francis.

634
00:33:54,200 --> 00:33:56,030
需要我给总理打电话吗
Do I need to call the prime minister?

635
00:33:56,030 --> 00:33:58,440
一通电话可能解决不了
Oh, I think it's gonna take more than a phone call.

636
00:33:58,930 --> 00:34:01,960
-说说吧  -其实我不是为这个来的
- Tell me. - That's not why I'm here, actually.

637
00:34:07,650 --> 00:34:09,480
这几个月的事太多
So much has been going on in the past few months,

638
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:10,960
咱俩都没时间聊聊了
we hardly have time to talk.

639
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:12,390
用这个
Here, use this.

640
00:34:15,200 --> 00:34:16,650
那晚你要睡我的床
I feel bad about the other night

641
00:34:16,650 --> 00:34:18,530
我不该赶你走
when you wanted to sleep in my bed.

642
00:34:18,530 --> 00:34:20,790
不用自责
Oh, that. You shouldn't.

643
00:34:21,530 --> 00:34:22,400
我就是
I just--

644
00:34:23,050 --> 00:34:25,390
我也不知道为什么在那边睡了
I don't know why I started sleeping in there.

645
00:34:25,850 --> 00:34:28,340
没记错的话是你感冒了
Well, if I remember correctly, you had a cold.

646
00:34:28,390 --> 00:34:30,000
但我为什么没回去
But why I stayed.

647
00:34:31,210 --> 00:34:32,670
你不用解释
You don't have to explain.

648
00:34:35,720 --> 00:34:36,930
我想说我爱你
I want you to know that I love you.

649
00:34:36,930 --> 00:34:37,960
不是因为这个
It has nothing to do with that.

650
00:34:37,960 --> 00:34:40,480
我像以前一样爱你
I love you... as much as ever.

651
00:34:43,750 --> 00:34:45,440
不用说了
Not another word.

652
00:34:50,030 --> 00:34:52,300
明早继续谈以色列的事吧
Let's finish talking about Israel in the morning.

653
00:34:54,370 --> 00:34:56,290
你说一通电话解决不了
You said more than a phone call?

654
00:34:59,010 --> 00:35:02,430
他们需要承诺  弗兰西斯  真会出兵
They need it in stone, Francis, that we'll contribute troops.

655
00:35:02,640 --> 00:35:05,320
-行政命令  -国会肯定不乐意
- An executive order. - Congress won't be happy.

656
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:07,280
反正已经不开心了
Well, they're already not happy.

657
00:35:07,550 --> 00:35:10,000
恶心了他们一次  就不在乎第二次了
I spat in one eye, I might as well spit in the other.

658
00:35:10,430 --> 00:35:11,610
没问题
Consider it done.

659
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:21,710
谢谢  谢谢你的支持
Thank you. Thank you for your support.

660
00:35:21,790 --> 00:35:24,050
非常感谢  谢谢
Thank you so much. Thank you.

661
00:35:24,060 --> 00:35:26,120
谢谢  可以啊
Thank you. Oh, sure.

662
00:35:31,220 --> 00:35:32,100
拍到了吗
Did you get it?

663
00:35:33,930 --> 00:35:36,450
谢谢  非常感谢
Thank you. Thank you so much.

664
00:35:36,700 --> 00:35:38,830
谢谢  谢谢你的支持
Thank you. Thank you for your support.

665
00:35:38,860 --> 00:35:39,570
谢谢你  先生
Thank you, sir.

666
00:35:39,570 --> 00:35:41,450
我喜欢你的演讲  邓巴女士
I liked your speech, Ms. Dunbar.

667
00:35:41,450 --> 00:35:42,810
我听过的演讲可多了
And I've heard more than a few.

668
00:35:42,810 --> 00:35:44,310
非常感谢  先生
I appreciate you saying that, sir.

669
00:35:44,310 --> 00:35:46,240
我知道爱荷华州人不容易取悦
I know Iowans aren't easily impressed.

670
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:48,120
你之前怎么说正直来着
What you said about integrity?

671
00:35:48,130 --> 00:35:49,660
你要是保证做位正直的总统
Well, if you can bring that to Washington,

672
00:35:49,660 --> 00:35:50,770
我党团会议就支持你
I'll caucus for you.

673
00:35:50,780 --> 00:35:53,770
一次争取一名支持者  选举就得这样
One supporter at a time. That's how we'll win this.

674
00:35:53,990 --> 00:35:57,450
那个小伙子  我替他难过  他令人振奋
And that young man? I feel for him. He's an inspiring individual.

675
00:35:57,450 --> 00:35:59,200
约翰  来见见这位先生
John, there's someone I want you to meet.

676
00:35:59,200 --> 00:36:01,070
-您叫什么  -克莱夫·雷诺兹
- Your name, sir? - Clive Reynolds.

677
00:36:01,070 --> 00:36:04,060
-雷诺兹先生  幸会  -我在为你丈夫祈祷
- Mr. Reynolds, nice to meet you. - I'm praying for your husband.

678
00:36:04,060 --> 00:36:06,120
他还在俄罗斯真是可惜
It's awful he's still stuck there.

679
00:36:07,090 --> 00:36:08,140
谢谢  雷诺兹先生
Thank you, Mr. Reynolds.

680
00:36:08,140 --> 00:36:09,300
-谢谢  -谢谢
- Thank you. - Thank you.

681
00:36:09,300 --> 00:36:12,490
谢谢你们的支持  谢谢你们前来
Thank you for your support. Thank you for coming out.

682
00:36:24,090 --> 00:36:25,730
打个电话就好了
You could've just called.

683
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:27,910
我讨厌在华盛顿过国庆
I hate July Fourth in DC.

684
00:36:28,980 --> 00:36:30,750
还想看看你怎么拉选票
Plus, I wanted to see you in action.

685
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:32,160
怎么样
What'd you think?

686
00:36:33,260 --> 00:36:34,440
她得离开
I need her to leave.

687
00:36:40,660 --> 00:36:41,920
车上见
I'll meet you at the car.

688
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,280
-希瑟  -辛西娅
- Heather-- - Cynthia.

689
00:37:07,520 --> 00:37:08,430
看看吧
Read that.

690
00:37:19,980 --> 00:37:22,190
安德伍德夫人要我毁掉
Mrs. Underwood asked me to destroy it.

691
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:24,970
-我没照做  -应该毁掉的
- I didn't. - You should have.

692
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:26,870
她在全国电视上说谎了
She lied on national television.

693
00:37:26,880 --> 00:37:29,540
我不会用这种手段竞选的
I am not running that sort of campaign.

694
00:37:31,990 --> 00:37:33,600
至少你知道手里有牌了
But it's good to know it's available.

695
00:37:33,910 --> 00:37:37,130
我绝不会那么对一个女人
I would never do that to another woman,

696
00:37:37,130 --> 00:37:38,800
辛西娅也不会
and neither would Cynthia.

697
00:37:39,820 --> 00:37:41,800
选辛西娅做竞选经理挺不错
Cynthia was a good choice for your manager.

698
00:37:41,970 --> 00:37:43,900
她肯定能经营好团队
She'll run a top-notch operation.

699
00:37:44,860 --> 00:37:46,540
但你需要有人做一些
But you need someone who's willing to do the things

700
00:37:46,540 --> 00:37:48,390
她下不去手的事
that people like her won't do.

701
00:37:49,120 --> 00:37:51,080
你要我聘用你的时候
When you asked me for a job,

702
00:37:51,600 --> 00:37:54,470
你说你想翻开新的一页
you said you wanted to turn over a new leaf.

703
00:37:55,230 --> 00:37:57,500
我的技能很固定  邓巴女士
I have a certain skill set, Ms. Dunbar.

704
00:37:58,010 --> 00:37:59,400
对我来说  翻开新的一页
For me, turning over a new leaf

705
00:37:59,400 --> 00:38:01,990
就是为好目的使用我的技能
is using my skills for the right reasons.

706
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:04,090
比如帮你当选
Like putting you in office.

707
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:07,780
15万  广告投入的1%
One-fifty. One point on the ad-buy.

708
00:38:09,280 --> 00:38:10,370
广告投入不行
No points.

709
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:13,960
但帮我赢得提名
But I'll do a hundred thousand win bonus

710
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:15,870
给你十万奖金
if we get the nomination.

711
00:38:30,340 --> 00:38:32,200
希望你是有好消息
I hope I came over here for some good news.

712
00:38:35,450 --> 00:38:37,530
我加入  告诉总统吧
I'm in. You can tell the president.

713
00:38:37,870 --> 00:38:39,090
8月19号
August 19th.

714
00:38:39,090 --> 00:38:41,680
我们需要的宣布时间比那早很多
We wanted you to announce a lot earlier than that.

715
00:38:41,680 --> 00:38:44,750
不  不是宣布参选  是这个
No, not the announcement. This.

716
00:38:48,660 --> 00:38:50,140
心脏病医生挺阔啊
Cardiology's good money.

717
00:38:50,990 --> 00:38:53,030
你不恭喜一下吗
Aren't you gonna say congrats?

718
00:38:54,380 --> 00:38:56,190
从没见你这么少女心
I've never seen you be this girly.

719
00:38:56,190 --> 00:38:59,370
这他妈是钻戒啊  少女一下怎么了
It's a fucking diamond. I'm allowed to be a little girly.

720
00:38:59,590 --> 00:39:01,670
恭喜  我为你们俩高兴
Congratulations. I'm happy for you both.

721
00:39:01,670 --> 00:39:02,640
真的吗
Are you?

722
00:39:07,190 --> 00:39:09,740
抱歉  我不该那么说
Sorry. That wasn't fair.

723
00:39:10,630 --> 00:39:13,340
也许我们该谈谈宣布竞选的时间
Maybe we should talk about dates for announcing the campaign.

724
00:39:13,780 --> 00:39:16,420
对  我想到几个时间  让我看下日程表
Yeah, I have a few ideas. Let me pull up my calendar.

725
00:39:21,310 --> 00:39:24,430
下下周似乎最合适
Week after next seems to be the best option.

726
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:25,660
你今晚有约吗
You have plans tonight?

727
00:39:27,150 --> 00:39:28,320
去看烟火
For the fireworks?

728
00:39:29,810 --> 00:39:31,990
艾伦和我准备带他的孩子一起去
Alan and I are taking his kids.

729
00:39:33,310 --> 00:39:35,100
好吧  也对
Right. Makes sense.

730
00:39:39,210 --> 00:39:42,950
你刚才说下下周吗
You were saying, about a week after next?

731
00:39:59,740 --> 00:40:02,690
-大使在里面  -你要我进去吗
- The Ambassador's inside. - You want me to go in there?

732
00:40:02,690 --> 00:40:04,330
她只是在化妆
She's just putting on makeup.

733
00:40:06,380 --> 00:40:08,190
我可以等她出来
I can wait until she comes out.

734
00:40:08,190 --> 00:40:11,330
她会直接去机场  如果您不介意的话
She's going straight to her plane. If you don't mind.

735
00:40:17,460 --> 00:40:18,500
亚历克西
Alexi.

736
00:40:26,310 --> 00:40:29,550
今天过得太快  我得马上去华盛顿
The day got away from me, so I have to head down to DC

737
00:40:29,560 --> 00:40:31,790
参加国庆庆祝活动
for the July Fourth celebration.

738
00:40:31,940 --> 00:40:34,870
你可以当我是男卫生间的大使
You may consider me an Ambassador from the men's room.

739
00:40:35,950 --> 00:40:38,200
别逗我笑  否则我就得重化
Don't make me laugh. I'll have to start over.

740
00:40:40,950 --> 00:40:43,180
-怎么样  -很美
- Good? - Quite.

741
00:40:43,960 --> 00:40:46,590
亚历克西  我们之前一直有敌意
Alexi, I think we've gotten off on the wrong foot.

742
00:40:47,340 --> 00:40:50,200
我们得找到更好的合作方法
We need to find a better way to work together.

743
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:52,210
你要撤回决议案吗
You're letting go of the resolution?

744
00:40:54,230 --> 00:40:56,420
-眼妆呢  -堪称完美
- Eyes? - Perfect.

745
00:40:56,710 --> 00:40:58,640
听听男人的看法总是好事
It's always nice to have a man's opinion.

746
00:40:59,680 --> 00:41:01,090
顺便说下  你是对的
You were right, by the way.

747
00:41:01,500 --> 00:41:04,230
只有我们派兵  以色列才会支持我们
Israel won't back us unless we commit troops.

748
00:41:04,370 --> 00:41:05,380
你识破了我的虚张声势  亚历克西
You called my bluff, Alexi,

749
00:41:05,380 --> 00:41:08,470
而我就不该如此  这是侮辱你
and I shouldn't have insulted you with one in the first place.

750
00:41:08,470 --> 00:41:10,000
我去外面等你了
I'll be outside when you finish.

751
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:12,620
总统今早签署了一份行政命令
The President signed an Executive Order this morning.

752
00:41:14,940 --> 00:41:17,370
五千名美国士兵被派去
Five thousand US military reassigned

753
00:41:17,370 --> 00:41:20,530
长久待命支援联合国维和行动
to permanent standby for UN Peacekeeping operations.

754
00:41:20,570 --> 00:41:22,280
耶路撒冷已知晓此事
Jerusalem has been informed.

755
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:24,440
你丈夫并没有这种权利
Your husband doesn't have that kind of authority.

756
00:41:24,440 --> 00:41:27,160
那是占领区  他并未向他国领土派兵
It's occupied territory. He's not deploying on sovereign land.

757
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:29,560
作为三军统帅
So, as Commander in Chief,

758
00:41:29,640 --> 00:41:31,970
他不需要得到国会批准
he doesn't need Congressional approval.

759
00:41:33,130 --> 00:41:34,860
以色列又与我们同一阵线了  亚历克西
Israel's back on board again, Alexi,

760
00:41:34,860 --> 00:41:37,440
只要你们向伊朗出售军火
so the moment you sell arms to Iran,

761
00:41:37,780 --> 00:41:40,190
我们会击落运输机  击翻货运卡车
we will shoot the planes out of the sky, the trucks off the road,

762
00:41:40,190 --> 00:41:41,890
击沉货船
and the ships out of the water.

763
00:41:42,180 --> 00:41:47,910
也许你们不怕遭到制裁
Now... maybe you'd be able to afford sanctions...

764
00:41:48,440 --> 00:41:50,870
但你们绝不敢挑起战争
but you sure as hell can't afford a war.

765
00:41:51,820 --> 00:41:54,910
重新回到谈判桌上来  与我们真诚谈判
Come back to the table. Engage us in good faith.

766
00:41:54,910 --> 00:41:57,230
否则下周决议案就将进入表决环节
Or the resolution goes to a vote next week.

767
00:41:57,930 --> 00:41:59,780
我一直很愿意与你磋商
I have always been willing to talk.

768
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:03,680
我不是说你与我  是总统间的对话
Not you and I. President to president.

769
00:42:03,970 --> 00:42:06,520
我们还需要你们释放迈克尔·科里根
Oh, and we need Michael Corrigan released, also.

770
00:42:10,410 --> 00:42:12,460
我会将你的意思传达给莫斯科
I'll communicate your message to Moscow.

771
00:42:12,460 --> 00:42:14,720
麻烦了  能给我递张纸巾吗
Please. Hand me a towel, would you?

772
00:42:21,360 --> 00:42:22,520
真有绅士风度
What a gentleman.

773
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:36,420
你以前来过白宫吗
You ever been to the White House before?

774
00:42:36,490 --> 00:42:38,310
赢得国家图书奖的时候来过
When I won the National Book Award.

775
00:42:39,130 --> 00:42:41,400
-南茜是书迷  -真是出乎我意料
- Nancy was a fan. - I'm surprised.

776
00:42:41,400 --> 00:42:44,360
那个故事可不怎么体现家庭价值观
That story doesn't exactly revere family values.

777
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:46,120
她流着占星家的血
She's got the astrologer in her.

778
00:42:46,660 --> 00:42:48,560
我觉得她最喜欢的就是标题
I think she liked the title more than anything.

779
00:42:48,560 --> 00:42:50,990
《天蝎》这书很不错
Scorpio was a very good book.

780
00:42:51,030 --> 00:42:54,010
-够糊口而已  -请坐
- Still pays the rent. - Have a seat.

781
00:42:54,020 --> 00:42:56,010
为什么让我来  总统先生
Why am I here, Mr. President?

782
00:42:56,670 --> 00:42:57,930
雷米跟你解释过
Remy briefed you.

783
00:42:58,780 --> 00:43:01,710
他说你需要本书  但没说题材是什么
He said you needed a book. He didn't say about what.

784
00:43:01,720 --> 00:43:02,900
关于《美国就业法案》
America Works.

785
00:43:02,900 --> 00:43:05,420
不只是政策本身  还有它的起源
Not just the policy, but the origins.

786
00:43:05,550 --> 00:43:07,940
一位出身贫寒的少年
How a boy grew up in a dirt-poor shithole

787
00:43:07,940 --> 00:43:10,460
是如何努力工作攀上人生巅峰
and climbed his way out through hard work.

788
00:43:10,460 --> 00:43:14,220
一个关于尊严的故事  努力工作所赢得的骄傲
A story of dignity. The pride that comes with one's labor.

789
00:43:14,220 --> 00:43:17,490
-政治宣传  -也可以这么说
- Propaganda. - You could call it that.

790
00:43:17,930 --> 00:43:20,990
这种文章  我并不擅长
This sort of thing... it's not in my wheelhouse.

791
00:43:20,990 --> 00:43:23,610
您需要推销员  而非小说家
You need a salesman, not a novelist.

792
00:43:24,860 --> 00:43:28,990
"不论你是谁  不论你以为自己是谁
"Whoever you are, whoever you think you are,

793
00:43:29,360 --> 00:43:33,410
想象你是位沉默的公主
believe that you're also a silent princess.

794
00:43:33,750 --> 00:43:35,700
名叫艾达
Your name is Ida.

795
00:43:36,120 --> 00:43:39,030
你的旅程发生在一个被人遗忘的世界
Your journey is one through a forgotten landscape

796
00:43:39,030 --> 00:43:42,790
那里满布了扭曲的阶梯和变形的城堡
of twisting staircases and morphing castles,

797
00:43:42,790 --> 00:43:47,300
你将踩着浮石去征服怒海狂涛
atop floating stones defiantly crossing an angry sea,

798
00:43:47,300 --> 00:43:51,260
探索废墟遍地的昏暗洞穴
within dimly-lit caverns cobwebbed with ruins

799
00:43:51,260 --> 00:43:55,410
{\pos(122,252)}荷兰版画家

800
00:43:51,260 --> 00:43:55,410
莫里茨·埃舍尔在梦中才能窥见这样的世界"
M.C. Escher could only grasp at in a dream state."

801
00:43:55,420 --> 00:43:57,530
您读过我写的游戏评测
You read my video game reviews?

802
00:43:57,530 --> 00:43:59,670
我经常玩清版射击游戏
I tend to play shoot-'em-ups.

803
00:43:59,670 --> 00:44:01,140
对独立游戏并不感兴趣
The indie games don't really interest me.

804
00:44:01,140 --> 00:44:02,490
我需要刺激与战斗
I need adrenaline and action.

805
00:44:02,490 --> 00:44:06,160
但当我读了这个  我一定要玩玩看
But when I read this, I had to try it.

806
00:44:06,430 --> 00:44:07,590
如果你仅用一百字
If you can convince me to

807
00:44:07,590 --> 00:44:10,350
就能说服我做一位沉默的公主
be a silent princess with just a hundred words,

808
00:44:10,350 --> 00:44:13,400
想想看你这本书将能说服多少人
imagine how many millions you can convince with this book.

809
00:44:13,400 --> 00:44:15,560
你就是推销员  托马斯
You are a salesman, Thomas.

810
00:44:15,560 --> 00:44:19,000
我没想推销什么  就是讲下我的感受
I wasn't trying to sell anything. Just describe my experience.

811
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:21,260
我也要你这么对待我的故事
That's exactly what I want you to do with my story.

812
00:44:21,260 --> 00:44:24,110
不要推销  只描述你的探究
No sales pitch, just your honest curiosity.

813
00:44:24,110 --> 00:44:28,050
再说  这种书一般都很无聊  保守
Besides, these kinds of books are always so boring, so safe.

814
00:44:28,050 --> 00:44:31,800
我想要点不同的  独特的
I want something different, something... unique.

815
00:44:32,510 --> 00:44:33,930
你的文笔
Your voice.

816
00:44:34,160 --> 00:44:36,710
我都不知道自己相不相信你的计划
I don't even know if I believe in your program.

817
00:44:38,020 --> 00:44:39,960
跟我来  给你看点东西
Come with me. I want to show you something.

818
00:44:42,470 --> 00:44:44,100
美国在招工

819
00:44:44,100 --> 00:44:45,140
美国在招工

820
00:44:45,140 --> 00:44:46,190
美国在招工

821
00:44:46,190 --> 00:44:47,480
美国在招工

822
00:44:47,480 --> 00:44:50,320
美国在招工

823
00:44:50,320 --> 00:44:53,360
美国在招工

824
00:44:53,360 --> 00:44:55,280
美国在招工

825
00:44:55,280 --> 00:44:58,490
美国在招工

826
00:44:58,490 --> 00:44:59,620
美国在招工

827
00:45:23,050 --> 00:45:24,950
搭起帐篷  大家自然会来
You build it and they come.

828
00:45:23,050 --> 00:45:29,700
{\pos(382,282)}{\an3}均取自电影《梦幻成真》
原片是指建造棒球场

829
00:45:25,710 --> 00:45:29,700
今天的国家广场是梦想之地
Today, the Washington Mall is the real Field of Dreams.

830
00:45:29,700 --> 00:45:31,820
今早开门之后
Three thousand people have registered

831
00:45:31,820 --> 00:45:33,150
来了三千人注册
since we set up shop this morning.

832
00:45:33,150 --> 00:45:35,970
这才叫国庆节聚会
Now that's what I call a Fourth of July party!

833
00:45:35,970 --> 00:45:39,770
这个聚会会不眠不休  一直办下去
And we're gonna keep the party going 'round the clock, 24/7,

834
00:45:39,770 --> 00:45:43,010
直到首都每个想求职的人
till everyone in DC who wants a job

835
00:45:43,210 --> 00:45:45,570
都来这里注册过
can make their way down here and sign up.

836
00:45:53,190 --> 00:45:54,090
看看吧
Have a look.

837
00:45:56,770 --> 00:46:01,200
-看到那队伍了吗  -《美就法》的帐篷
- Do you see that line of people? - The AmWorks tent.

838
00:46:01,200 --> 00:46:03,490
从那儿一直延伸到林肯纪念堂
It stretches from there all the way to the Lincoln Memorial.

839
00:46:03,500 --> 00:46:06,110
天还没亮就开始排队了
They started lining up before sunrise.

840
00:46:07,680 --> 00:46:08,790
真了不起
It's really something.

841
00:46:09,270 --> 00:46:11,620
托马斯  帮不了他们  我成了历史的脚注
Thomas, at best, I'm going to be a footnote in history

842
00:46:11,620 --> 00:46:14,450
那都算好  搞不好还会沦为笑柄
if I can't help those people. At worst, I'll be a joke.

843
00:46:14,460 --> 00:46:16,020
我跟他们一样
I am those people.

844
00:46:16,020 --> 00:46:17,980
我希望你把这个写下来
I want you to tell that story.

845
00:46:18,870 --> 00:46:19,880
怎么样
What do you say?

846
00:46:21,150 --> 00:46:23,840
-不知道  -你的直觉呢
- I don't know. - What's your gut say?

847
00:46:24,980 --> 00:46:28,040
你的话好像不太对劲  但我很感兴趣
That you don't add up, and I'm intrigued.

848
00:46:28,040 --> 00:46:30,380
-但还没说服你  -还没
- But not sold. - Not yet.

849
00:46:30,470 --> 00:46:32,310
钱是肯定不会少了你的
Well, I'll pay you well, and at the very least,

850
00:46:32,310 --> 00:46:34,720
这种活儿一向能捞一笔  是吧
this sort of access is worth its weight in gold, isn't it?

851
00:46:34,720 --> 00:46:35,960
先生  第一夫人回来了
Sir, the First Lady's back.

852
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:38,590
我得在放焰火之前致辞
I have to go give my Fourth of July speech before the fireworks.

853
00:46:38,590 --> 00:46:41,470
-您要多久写完  -一月之前
- How quickly would you need the book? - By January.

854
00:46:41,470 --> 00:46:43,360
我写东西一向要一年多
I've never written anything in less than a year.

855
00:46:43,360 --> 00:46:44,330
我看你的样子
Well, you don't strike me

856
00:46:44,330 --> 00:46:46,710
不像遇到挑战就会退缩
as someone who shies away from a challenge.

857
00:46:48,200 --> 00:46:50,430
我得按我自己的方式写
I'd need to be able to write it the way I want to write it.

858
00:46:50,450 --> 00:46:53,610
没问题  多待一会儿  看看风景
Absolutely. Look, take your time. Enjoy the view.

859
00:46:53,610 --> 00:46:55,220
看完了密查姆会送你出去
Meechum will show you out when you're done.

860
00:46:55,220 --> 00:46:59,200
我保证  你答应了绝不会后悔
And I promise, if you say yes, you won't regret it.

861
00:47:01,530 --> 00:47:04,520
有水平的作家都不会拒绝好故事
No writer worth his salt can resist a good story,

862
00:47:04,820 --> 00:47:08,540
就像政客总忍不住乱许诺言一样
just as no politician can resist making promises he can't keep.

863
00:47:17,010 --> 00:47:19,840
维克多  受邀前往是我们的荣幸
Viktor, we'd be honored to accept the invitation.

864
00:47:20,750 --> 00:47:23,670
是啊  要谈的事太多了
Yes, I agree, there's much to discuss.

865
00:47:24,570 --> 00:47:26,410
我会叫我的办公室联系克里姆林宫
I'll have my office reach out to the Kremlin.

866
00:47:26,410 --> 00:47:28,560
安排一个都方便的日期
We'll find dates that work for both of us.

867
00:47:30,330 --> 00:47:31,280
谢谢
Thank you.

868
00:47:32,070 --> 00:47:34,480
你该睡了吧  那边都好晚了
Well, you should get some sleep. It's late over there.

869
00:47:36,080 --> 00:47:36,990
晚安
Good night.

870
00:47:38,680 --> 00:47:40,060
表决暂缓
Hold off on the vote?

871
00:47:40,490 --> 00:47:43,410
等谈了再说  不过留着这一手
Until we sit down. But we keep it in our back pocket.

872
00:47:43,990 --> 00:47:45,180
迈克尔·科里根呢
Michael Corrigan?

873
00:47:46,250 --> 00:47:48,200
我们到访的时候释放他
They're going to release him when we visit.

874
00:47:48,820 --> 00:47:50,440
你造就了奇迹
You made a miracle happen.

875
00:47:51,120 --> 00:47:52,060
是我们
We did.

876
00:48:00,950 --> 00:48:04,090
每一位独一无二的公民都影响着未来
...each unique citizen contributes to our future.

877
00:48:04,090 --> 00:48:05,100
能大点声吗
Can you turn that up?

878
00:48:05,100 --> 00:48:08,440
我们的先辈宣布独立时
Our forefathers, when they declared independence,

879
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:11,410
就理解个体的力量
understood the power of the individual,

880
00:48:11,410 --> 00:48:14,190
自主的价值
the value of self-determination.

881
00:48:14,190 --> 00:48:16,600
他们把我们从暴政中解放出来
They freed us from tyranny.

882
00:48:16,600 --> 00:48:18,020
-他们证明了...  -他就是暴君
- They proved... - He is a tyrant.

883
00:48:18,020 --> 00:48:19,890
不好说  那里那么多人
I don't know, there's a lot of people out there.

884
00:48:19,890 --> 00:48:21,210
他也许做对了
He might be onto something.

885
00:48:21,210 --> 00:48:23,610
下行政命令调派维和部队  他疯了吧
Executive Order for UN troops? He's out of control.

886
00:48:23,610 --> 00:48:26,170
至少他有所行动  沃克什么都没干
At least he's doing something. Walker didn't do shit.

887
00:48:26,170 --> 00:48:28,920
我们弹劾了个哑炮  换了个原子弹
I think we replaced a dud with an atom bomb.

888
00:48:29,260 --> 00:48:32,020
他们的自由是抗争得来的
They had to fight to secure their freedom.

889
00:48:32,030 --> 00:48:35,330
如今我们也要通过抗争保住自由
And now we have to fight to maintain it.

890
00:48:35,330 --> 00:48:37,430
工作的自由
The freedom to work.

891
00:48:37,430 --> 00:48:40,310
体面活着的自由
The freedom to live with dignity.

892
00:48:40,310 --> 00:48:42,910
希望的自由
The freedom to hope.

893
00:48:43,010 --> 00:48:47,560
谢谢你们  天佑美国
Thank you, and God bless the United States of America.

894
00:49:33,870 --> 00:49:43,870
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}奥巴马上任后最重要的一个法案
是被称为"奥巴马医改"(Obamacare)的《医疗改革法案》
在经过艰苦的谈判后  这个法案被带到参众两院进行投票
按正常程序  法案需要经过至少两轮投票
在投票过程中要进行一些修改
当时奥巴马所属的民主党在参众两院都处于多数党位置
法案通过似乎没有悬念
但在投票开始后  马萨诸塞州一名民主党参议员突然过世
补选上来的是一名共和党议员
这使民主党在参议院失去了绝对多数
奥巴马费尽心血的法案面临夭折的风险
这时  在奥巴马的支持下
众议院议长佩洛西将这个旨在改革医疗政策的法案
定性为"预算法案"  从而避免了这个法案在参议院进行新的投票
"奥巴马医改"靠这个不是很光明正大的办法成为了法律

